title: For Sale/Trade:  WTT QUAD for Gun
postcontent: Available for trade for a firearm:  1994 Suzuki Quad Runner 4x4, with 364 original miles.  I inherited the Suzuki from my father a few years ago when he passed away.   I had the quad serviced (oil change and new battery) when I brought it here from Vermont, registered it, drove it a few miles, and it has sat in my garage since.  It currently does not start, and a rear tire has gone flat- I think it got a thorn in it while driving it on my property.  Because it doesn’t start, I’m selling it “as is”.  As you can see from the low mileage, it wasn’t used much (for hunting only), but the down side was my dad stored outside for some time, accounting for the rust on the metal, and the seat cover deteriorating.   The ATV, aside from the surface rust and seat cover, is in quite good condition.  The body is free of cracks & dents.  If you are mechanically inclined, this is quite a find.  I am looking to trade the ATV even up for a firearm.  Please tell me what you have to trade, I prefer “new in box” or “like new in box”, but am open to any rifle, shotgun or pistol.  Please let me know what you have, and I will trade when the right deal becomes available.  The ATV (and it’s owner) are NY residents, so the firearm will need to go through an FFL.   The NY DMV didn’t issue a title- (they said the registration will allow for legal ownership transfer) and a bill of sale will be included.

Here we have the absolutely awesome Heckler & Koch MR762A1 .308 Tactical Semi Automatic Rifle. This Rifle Is Brand New, In Stock & Ready To Ship !

Like its 5.56 mm counterpart, the MR762A1 is a direct descendent of the HK416/417 series, only in a semi-automatic rifle configuration developed for civilian users.

Using the HK-proprietary operating system, the MR762A1 is gas operated and uses a piston and a solid operating “pusher” rod in place of the common gas tube normally employed in AR15/M16/M4-style weapons. Pioneered by Heckler & Koch in the G36, HK416, and HK417; this method virtually eliminates malfunctions common to direct impingement gas systems since hot carbon fouling and waste gases do not enter the receiver area. The MR762A1 stays cleaner, reducing heat transfer to the bolt and bolt carrier, and drastically reducing wear and tear on other critical components. The service life of all parts is increased substantially. The MR762A1 uses a barrel produced by Heckler & Koch's famous cold hammer forging process. This manufacturing process uses the highest quality steel, producing a barrel that ensures superior accuracy, even after firing thousands of rounds.

The M4 RAS is a drop-in replacement part for standard, 2-piece polymer, M4-type handguards. title: For Sale:  Price Reduced - Mauser 66 in 30-06
postcontent:
This is a Mauser 66 chambered in 30-06 and in very nice condition. It currently wears an elevation adjustable rear sight with a hooded front sight. I have very poor eyesight and have never shot an iron-sighted rifle well at all. My first three shots through this rifle went into a half-inch at 40 yards with fading daylight. It shot so well with the open sights that I never ended up putting a scope on it. It will accept scope mounts, however. The rear base will fit onto two drilled-and-tapped holes in the receiver ring, while the front base should fit into the place currently filled with the rear sight.

The stock has great figure, with the straight grain having prominent regions of light and dark. This straight grain also makes the stock as strong as possible. The checkering is well-done, as is the rosewood end-cap. The monte-carlo cheekpiece places my eyes in just the right place to use the open sights, either shooting left or right handed. The trigger has no discernible creep, and breaks like glass. It is the best trigger that I have ever felt on a rifle.

The only things that keep this rifle from being in completely mint condition are:
•	There are a few minor and small indentations in the stock. These are all very small and do not go through the finish at all; they merely make a slight dimple in the gloss finish.
•	The buttpad is worn. If you need a soft and pliable buttpad, you will want to place a new pad on it. I used a slip-on Pachmyr decelerator pad for a few shots, and it fit well. I ended up taking it off though, as I found recoil with this rifle to be a non-issue.
•	There is a small chip and slight discoloration on the bottom of the gripcap. Again, this is only cosmetic, but I wanted to mention it.

This rifle is a very cool concept. It is only about 41.5” long, despite having a 24” barrel. This is about 3” shorter than most bolt actions. The principle is similar to the straight-pull Blasers and the Merkel KR1. The bolt sits on a rail system, with a receiver piece integral with the bolt body. This entire assembly moves rearward when you pull the bolt back. This rail system allows you to fit a long action cartridge like a 30-06 into a short (308) length action. Additionally, the magazine is moved from the more traditional location in front of the trigger-guard to directly above the trigger. This saves a couple of inches in rifle length for a given barrel length.

This action cycles smooth and feels like it locks up like a bank vault. Despite being very strongly built, it weighs only about 7.4 pounds in its present configuration. This would make a great hunting rifle, as it is strong, accurate, and compact. If you would like more images or images of a specific spot, let me know and I will email them to you. This is one of the most interesting and innovative rifle designs that I have ever seen.

I am happy to ship the rifle to your local FFL, but the buyer will be responsible for all shipping and FFL costs. Additionally, if your FFL does not accept transfers from individuals, add $40 for me to cover my FFL's fee.
